# Folder structure (Next.js app)

## Target layout

```txt
public/
  images/  icons/  favicons/

src/
  app/
    (marketing)/  (auth)/  (dashboard)/
    api/
    globals.css  layout.tsx  not-found.tsx  robots.ts  sitemap.ts
  components/
    ui/           # Level 1 — primitives
    common/       # Level 2 — shared
    layout/       # Level 2 — shell pieces
    marketing/    # Level 3 — domain
    auth/
    dashboard/
  sections/       # Full-width page sections (compose ui + domain components)
  features/       # Optional feature modules (when useful)
  data/
  hooks/
  lib/
  constants/
  types/
  styles/         # Optional extra styles
```

## Component levels

1. **`components/ui/`** — button, input, textarea, select, badge, card, avatar, tabs, accordion, modal, switch, tooltip.
2. **`components/common/` + `layout/`** — section-heading, page-hero, breadcrumb, theme-toggle, social-links, pagination, main-navbar, main-footer, mobile-menu.
3. **`components/marketing|auth|dashboard/`** — pricing-card, testimonial-card, auth-shell, dashboard-sidebar, etc.

## Sections

- **`src/sections/<area>/`** — e.g. `sections/pricing/pricing-hero.tsx`; page-specific composition lives here; **kebab-case** files, **PascalCase** exports.

## Naming

- Files: **kebab-case** (`pricing-card.tsx`).
- Exports: **PascalCase** (`PricingCard`).
- Name by **purpose**, not appearance.
